  <prompt>
    Verify that parallel project `spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6` has completed its closeout tasks 089 (R6 PCF redeploy) and 090 (R6 UAT regression) before this project begins Phase 0 cleanup. This is a HARD GATE: if R6 closeout is incomplete, downstream code edits in this worktree risk colliding with R6 hotfix commits. Produce a handoff confirmation note documenting evidence.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform coordinator. Verifies cross-project prerequisites via TASK-INDEX inspection + git log + PR status.</role>

  <goal>
    A confirmation handoff note at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/notes/handoffs/000-r6-readiness-confirmation.md` stating: (a) R6 task 089 status, (b) R6 task 090 status, (c) UAT regression test outcome, (d) any open R6 hotfix PRs (especially PR #401) and their merge ETA. If any prerequisite is incomplete, this task BLOCKS waves 0-A and downstream phases until cleared.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per CLAUDE.md §3 (project context) and TASK-INDEX cross-wave dependency exceptions table, R6 closeout is a hard prereq before this project edits files in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/` or `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`. R6 PR #401 is also a Phase 7 cutover gate. Verifying R6 status early surfaces blockers before parallel Phase 0/1 waves dispatch.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
